Poland’s upcoming friendly against Nigeria is a perfect preparation for World Cup, according to goalie Wojciech Szczesny. The Eagles have drawn Senegal, Colombia and Japan in Group H of the World Cup. And Juventus goalkeeper Szczesny, believes their inexperience against African teams can be corrected against Nigeria. “We [Poland] definitely lack experience when it comes to playing with teams from Asia and Africa,” Szczesny told Polsat Sport.  “At this stage of preparation, everything is thought out and help us implement tactical assumptions and practice setting against teams, which way of playing are similar to those we will face in a group.” The post Szczesny: Poland Playing Nigeria Good For World Cup Preparation appeared first on 360Nobs.com. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.